content:
Other Improvements in Territory Planning

Better predict legend behaviors, clone datasets using the names of your choice, and recall the setting for including unassigned units in alignments in Territory Planning.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

Legend panel

* Adjust the size of the legend and preserve it even after changing the size of the browser and returning to alignments.
* Filter data, create rules, and assign units by selecting fields and their values from Salesforce instead of entering the values manually.

Dataset and alignment cloning

* When cloning datasets and alignments, name them during the cloning process instead of having to first save them and then change their names.

Unassigned units in alignments

* Control whether unassigned units appear when opening alignments for the first time.
* Territory Planning now recalls whether to include unassigned units when returning to alignments.

Boundaries in datasets

* Territory Planning includes updated boundaries so that you plan territories with the latest and most accurate ones.
title: Territory Planning Improvements in Salesforce
